00:39:21,420 --> 00:39:24,840
Let's forget about that.
Let's get back to the point.

479
00:39:25,430 --> 00:39:28,300
- Sorry.
- It's all right. It's all right.

480
00:39:28,470 --> 00:39:30,760
Okay, Mr. Markum.

481
00:39:30,930 --> 00:39:34,430
- Okay.
- Okay. All right. So, Jimmy...

482
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:39,060
...outside of the look Katie gave you,
was there anything else?

483
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:48,450
There was this kid.

484
00:39:48,660 --> 00:39:51,080
What am I talking about?
That was this morning.

485
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:53,370
What? Remember, it's the little things.

486
00:39:53,910 --> 00:39:57,960
This kid Brendan Harris come in the store,
like he was expecting to see her.

487
00:39:58,130 --> 00:40:00,920
- Barely knew each other.
- Could they have been dating?

488
00:40:01,090 --> 00:40:02,880
[JIMMY] No.
- What makes you so sure?

489
00:40:03,050 --> 00:40:05,590
Sean, are you gonna grill me?
A father knows.

490
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:08,550
Mrs. Markum, was Katie seeing anyone?

491
00:40:08,930 --> 00:40:12,010
No one right now, as far as we know.

492
00:40:12,180 --> 00:40:15,270
- I mean, knew.
- I'll give you whatever you need tomorrow.

493
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:18,730
We got girls at home wanting to know
where their sister is.

494
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:23,530
All right, there will be a trooper
downstairs to take you home.

495
00:40:24,570 --> 00:40:28,030
And if you think of anything...

496
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:31,870
...anything at all, give us a call.

497
00:40:37,750 --> 00:40:40,170
He said you almost got into a car
when you were kids?

498
00:40:40,340 --> 00:40:44,250
Shit. Me, Jimmy and a kid named Boyle
were playing in front of my house.

499
00:40:44,420 --> 00:40:46,300
This car came up and took Dave away.

500
00:40:46,470 --> 00:40:49,300
- Abduction?
- Yeah, guys pretending to be cops.

501
00:40:49,470 --> 00:40:53,720
Convinced Dave to get in the car,
kept him for four days before he escaped.

502
00:40:53,890 --> 00:40:55,720
- They catch these guys?
- One died.

503
00:40:55,890 --> 00:40:58,770
The other got busted,
went the noose route in his cell.

504
00:40:58,940 --> 00:41:02,940
Your pal Markum, the moment I laid
eyes on him, I could tell he'd done time.

505
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:06,280
They never lose that tension,
it settles in their shoulders.

506
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:09,200
He lost his daughter.
That's what's in his shoulders.

507
00:41:09,370 --> 00:41:13,740
No, that's in his stomach.
The tension in his shoulders, that's prison.

508
00:41:18,830 --> 00:41:21,670
Cause of death - The gunshot wound
to the back of the head...

509
00:41:21,840 --> 00:41:23,800
...not the trauma from the beating.

510
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:25,380
What else?

511
00:41:25,590 --> 00:41:28,130
[WHITEY]
Her and her friends were barhopping.

512
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:31,340
We're interviewing anyone
who might have seen them.

513
00:41:31,510 --> 00:41:34,140
One other thing,
the backpack in her car...

514
00:41:34,310 --> 00:41:37,310
...had pamphlets on Las Vegas
and a list of Vegas hotels.

515
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:39,770
It doesn't sound like much.

516
00:41:39,940 --> 00:41:42,150
What do you say, Devine?

517
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:45,570
We'll get the guy, sir.

518
00:41:45,990 --> 00:41:49,860
That's right. All right, let's do it.

519
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:57,790
- That's the best you can come up with?
- It made him happy, didn't it?

520
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,870
[Phone Rings]

521
00:42:00,830 --> 00:42:02,790
This is Sean.

522
00:42:03,590 --> 00:42:06,960
- Hello?
- Is it Lauren?

523
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:12,550
You're in Manhattan.
I can tell by the traffic sounds.

524
00:42:15,020 --> 00:42:16,720
Is he with you?

525
00:42:20,060 --> 00:42:22,650
[Tapping Through Phone]

526
00:42:23,270 --> 00:42:25,440
Is that the baby?

527
00:42:26,860 --> 00:42:28,990
Christ, Lauren, at least tell me her name.

528
00:42:38,830 --> 00:42:41,500
Yeah, nice talking to you too.

529
00:42:41,830 --> 00:42:44,920
[Chattering]

530
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:51,340
 [Piano Plays] 

531
00:42:55,430 --> 00:42:57,060
[WOMAN]
Hey.

532
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:02,850
[MAN 1]
Would it surprise you?

533
00:43:03,020 --> 00:43:04,940
[VAL]
Wouldn't be the first time.

534
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:11,070
[MAN 2] Did you see that girl?
Did you see that...?

535
00:43:11,240 --> 00:43:13,240
Did you see her?

536
00:43:13,700 --> 00:43:16,740
- I heard a car hit something.
- Hit what? Another car?

537
00:43:16,910 --> 00:43:19,790
- Oh, no, not loud like that.
- Like hitting the curb?

538
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,830
Yes, maybe.

539
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,960
Then it stalled, and someone said, "Hi."

540
00:43:25,130 --> 00:43:27,250
- Someone said, "Hi"?
- "Hi."

541
00:43:28,710 --> 00:43:30,930
Then there was a loud crack.

542
00:43:31,090 --> 00:43:34,800
- Could it have been a gunshot?
- Yes, maybe.

543
00:43:34,970 --> 00:43:38,350
- Did you look out your window?
PRIOR; Oh, no.

544
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:41,480
I was in my dressing gown by then.

545
00:43:42,270 --> 00:43:45,110
I don't look out the window
in my dressing gown.

546
00:43:45,270 --> 00:43:47,940
The voice you heard,
was that a male or a female?

547
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:50,570
Female.

548
00:43:50,740 --> 00:43:52,110
I think.

549
00:43:52,950 --> 00:43:56,030
- It sounds like the girl knew the shooter.
- Yeah.

550
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:58,450
Sorry to trouble you.

551
00:44:00,750 --> 00:44:03,210
[Doorbell Rings]

552
00:44:06,460 --> 00:44:08,920
- Jimmy.
- Theo.

553
00:44:09,090 --> 00:44:11,420
How's my daughter?
How's Annabeth holding up?

554
00:44:11,590 --> 00:44:13,590
- She's trying.
- Let's get these on ice.

555
00:44:13,760 --> 00:44:16,140
You got a couple of coolers?

556
00:44:22,100 --> 00:44:24,310
[THEO]
Right here's fine.

557
00:44:29,490 --> 00:44:32,860
So how are you handling all this so far?

558
00:44:33,030 --> 00:44:35,990
- It hasn't really sunk in, Theo.
- Yeah?

559
00:44:36,160 --> 00:44:38,580
It's gonna hurt like hell when it does.

560
00:44:38,750 --> 00:44:42,500
When my Janey died,
I was no good for six months...

561
00:44:42,670 --> 00:44:46,460
...but my kids were
all grown up. I had that luxury.

562
00:44:46,630 --> 00:44:50,340
You, you got domestic responsibilities.

563
00:44:52,430 --> 00:44:54,340
Domestic responsibilities?

564
00:44:54,510 --> 00:44:59,810
Yeah, you gotta take care of my daughter
and those girls. That's your first priority.

565
00:45:00,390 --> 00:45:02,980
Oh, you figured that might
have slipped my mind?

566
00:45:03,140 --> 00:45:05,730
It just needed to be said, that's all.

567
00:45:06,860 --> 00:45:09,980
You'll come through
because you're a man.

568
00:45:10,150 --> 00:45:12,320
Like I said to Annabeth,
your wedding day.

569
00:45:12,490 --> 00:45:15,740
I said, "You got yourself
a real old-school man there."

570
00:45:15,910 --> 00:45:18,530
- Like they put her in a bag.
[THEO] What?

571
00:45:18,700 --> 00:45:21,910
That's what Katie looked like
when I saw her in the morgue.

572
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:26,040
Like they put her in a bag
and then they beat the bag with pipes.

573
00:45:27,290 --> 00:45:29,880
- Well...
- Janey died in her sleep, all due respect.

574
00:45:30,050 --> 00:45:33,220
She went to sleep,
she never woke up. Peaceful.

575
00:45:33,550 --> 00:45:38,260
- You don't need to talk about Janey.
- My daughter was murdered.

576
00:45:38,430 --> 00:45:42,100
They put a gun to her. As we
stand here, she's on an autopsy slab...

577
00:45:42,270 --> 00:45:45,060
...getting cut open by scalpels
and chest spreaders...

578
00:45:45,230 --> 00:45:48,900
...and you're talking to me
about domestic fucking responsibility?

579
00:45:52,740 --> 00:45:54,950
Good to see you, Theo.

580
00:45:59,080 --> 00:46:02,580
Eve, just tell them what they
want to know.

581
00:46:02,750 --> 00:46:05,710
[SEAN] Who was she dating?
- We already told the Savages.

582
00:46:05,870 --> 00:46:08,630
[SEAN] The Savage brothers?
- They were here yesterday.

583
00:46:08,790 --> 00:46:12,170
Good, now try us out.
Who was she dating?

584
00:46:12,340 --> 00:46:14,630
No one special.

585
00:46:18,010 --> 00:46:21,260
You guys were having
a goodbye dinner, right?

586
00:46:22,020 --> 00:46:24,390
- What?
- She was leaving town, wasn't she?

587
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:27,940
- Going to Las Vegas?
- How do you know?

588
00:46:28,110 --> 00:46:32,940
She closed her bank account,
she had hotel phone numbers.

589
00:46:33,940 --> 00:46:37,110
She wanted out of this dump.
She wanted to start a new life.

590
00:46:37,450 --> 00:46:40,780
Well, a 19-year-old girl
doesn't go to Las Vegas alone.

591
00:46:41,490 --> 00:46:43,830
So who was she going with?

592
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:48,080
Come on, girls.
Who was she going with?

593
00:46:48,960 --> 00:46:50,250
Brendan.

594
00:46:50,590 --> 00:46:52,630
Excuse me?

595
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:56,170
- Brendan.
- Brendan Harris?

596
00:46:56,630 --> 00:46:58,800
Brendan Harris, yeah.

597
00:46:59,010 --> 00:47:00,800
You got an address?

598
00:47:05,770 --> 00:47:08,690
[Dog Barking]

599
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:16,280
[JIMMY]
Hey, Dave.

600
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:22,080
Hey, Jimmy.

601
00:47:22,240 --> 00:47:25,710
Sorry, I came out for a smoke.

602
00:47:26,540 --> 00:47:29,420
Go ahead, sit down. Sit down.

603
00:47:35,010 --> 00:47:38,010
I haven't had a chance
to talk to you all day.

604
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:43,180
How you doing?

605
00:47:44,730 --> 00:47:46,600
What happened to your hand?

606
00:47:47,520 --> 00:47:49,100
This?

607
00:47:50,060 --> 00:47:54,360
I was helping a buddy move a couch.
I slammed it in the doorjamb.

608
00:47:55,530 --> 00:47:58,200
Ways you can manage
to hurt yourself, right?

609
00:48:00,530 --> 00:48:02,200
It's good to see you.

610
00:48:02,990 --> 00:48:04,330
Yeah?

611
00:48:10,380 --> 00:48:12,540
How are our girls holding up?

612
00:48:12,710 --> 00:48:14,840
[DAVE]
They're doing okay, I guess.

613
00:48:15,010 --> 00:48:18,340
That Celeste, she's a godsend.
You thank her for me, will you?

614
00:48:30,110 --> 00:48:34,020
It's nice, isn't it? Just to sit out here.

615
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:37,610
Yeah.

616
00:48:42,580 --> 00:48:46,580
I couldn't stand looking through the
fridge to find room for all that food...

617
00:48:46,750 --> 00:48:49,710
...we're gonna throw away
in the next few days.

618
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:53,210
- Lot of waste, huh?
- Yeah.

619
00:48:54,590 --> 00:48:58,840
I just can't let anything get fucked up
in these next few days.

620
00:48:59,430 --> 00:49:03,930
Because it's all anybody
will remember about her.

621
00:49:10,190 --> 00:49:13,610
One thing you could say about Katie,
even when she was little...

622
00:49:14,820 --> 00:49:16,900
...that girl was neat.

623
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:21,820
When I got out of the joint...

624
00:49:23,200 --> 00:49:26,120
...you know, after Marita died...

625
00:49:27,620 --> 00:49:32,630
...I remember, I was more afraid
of my little daughter...

626
00:49:33,790 --> 00:49:36,460
...than I ever was of being in prison.

627
00:49:44,930 --> 00:49:47,140
I loved her...

628
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:50,350
...most...

629
00:49:53,020 --> 00:49:56,530
...because when we were sitting in that
kitchen that night...

630
00:49:59,400 --> 00:50:05,530
...it was like we were the last two
people on Earth. You know, forgotten.

631
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:08,330
Unwanted.

632
00:50:10,420 --> 00:50:14,790
And it's really starting to piss me off,
Dave, because I can't cry for her.

633
00:50:14,960 --> 00:50:19,050
My own little daughter,
and I can't even cry for her.

634
00:50:24,010 --> 00:50:25,810
Jimmy.

635
00:50:29,940 --> 00:50:31,810
You're crying now.

636
00:50:35,020 --> 00:50:37,190
Yeah, damn.

637
00:50:42,240 --> 00:50:45,200
I just want to hug her one more time.

638
00:50:48,910 --> 00:50:52,620
She was 19 fucking years old.

639
00:50:59,920 --> 00:51:01,880
Do you want me to leave you alone?

640
00:51:02,880 --> 00:51:05,430
No, just stay here for a minute,
if that's cool.

641
00:51:06,600 --> 00:51:10,220
Yeah, sure. Jimmy, it's cool.

642
00:51:27,030 --> 00:51:29,870
When was the last time
you saw Katie Markum?

643
00:51:30,160 --> 00:51:33,620
- You don't think I'd hurt her do you?
- She isn't hurt. She's dead.

644
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:40,590
- I didn't kill her.
- Again, when's the last time you saw her?

645
00:51:42,800 --> 00:51:46,090
About 8...
Saturday night, about 8:00.

646
00:51:46,390 --> 00:51:48,390
About like 8, Brendan, or at 8?

647
00:51:49,100 --> 00:51:50,930
It was about 8. Um...

648
00:51:51,930 --> 00:51:56,940
We had a couple slices at Hi-Fi,
and she had to go meet Eve and Diane.

649
00:51:57,270 --> 00:52:00,610
Yeah. Why doesn't Jimmy Markum
like you?

650
00:52:02,150 --> 00:52:03,820
I don't know.

651
00:52:04,740 --> 00:52:09,450
But he told Katie he never wanted her
to see me or any other Harris.

652
00:52:09,620 --> 00:52:13,540
What? That thief thinks he's better
than our family?

653
00:52:13,710 --> 00:52:15,210
He's not a thief.

654
00:52:15,380 --> 00:52:18,000
MRS. HARRIS:
He's a thief! A scumbag burglar.

655
00:52:18,590 --> 00:52:22,340
Daughter probably had the same bad
gene. You count yourself lucky, Bren.

656
00:52:23,090 --> 00:52:27,640
So Katie had some brochures for Vegas.
We heard she was going there with you.

657
00:52:29,310 --> 00:52:31,810
We were gonna leave Sunday.

658
00:52:33,020 --> 00:52:35,940
We were gonna get married
when we got there.

659
00:52:38,150 --> 00:52:40,520
Well, that was the plan, right?

660
00:52:40,820 --> 00:52:43,690
You were gonna leave me?
Without a word?

661
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:46,990
- Ma, I was gonna tell you.
- Just like your father, huh?

662
00:52:48,620 --> 00:52:51,450
[Door Opens]

663
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:58,170
That's my brother, Ray,
and his friend John.

664
00:52:58,340 --> 00:53:00,710
[SEAN] Hey, boys.
[JOHN] Hey.

665
00:53:00,960 --> 00:53:02,670
MRS. HARRIS:
He don't speak.

666
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:07,180
Father couldn't shut up, but his son's
a mute. Oh, yeah, life's fucking fair.

667
00:53:07,350 --> 00:53:11,470
They're here about Katie. Why don't you
go watch TV or something.

668
00:53:12,770 --> 00:53:16,980
So where were you between 12:30
and 2 a.m. On Sunday morning, Brendan?

669
00:53:17,810 --> 00:53:19,060
I was asleep.

670
00:53:19,230 --> 00:53:21,020
Can you confirm that, Mrs. Harris?

671
00:53:24,700 --> 00:53:27,990
I can confirm that he closed his door
at 10:00.

672
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:30,950
He came down for breakfast at 9.

673
00:53:31,790 --> 00:53:36,420
I can't confirm that he didn't open
his window and go down the fire escape.

674
00:53:36,580 --> 00:53:40,750
Okay, we're gonna ask you to take a
polygraph. You think you're up for that?

675
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:45,970
I loved her so much.

676
00:53:48,050 --> 00:53:50,760
I'm never gonna feel that again.

677
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:53,730
It doesn't happen twice.

678
00:53:55,980 --> 00:53:58,190
Doesn't happen once most times.

679
00:53:59,730 --> 00:54:01,570
Celeste.

680
00:54:02,690 --> 00:54:06,740
- Sorry, Jimmy. You surprised me.
- What are you still doing here?

681
00:54:07,070 --> 00:54:08,910
Uh...

682
00:54:09,580 --> 00:54:11,200
I don't know.

683
00:54:11,990 --> 00:54:15,000
I don't know, I just...

684
00:54:16,170 --> 00:54:18,040
Did Annabeth get to sleep?

685
00:54:18,380 --> 00:54:20,920
Yeah, I convinced her to take a pill.

686
00:54:21,090 --> 00:54:24,090
- Could I get one of those?
- Yeah.

687
00:54:29,260 --> 00:54:31,720
One for the road and then home.

688
00:54:36,100 --> 00:54:40,770
Jimmy, I can stay over if you want.
Sit up with Annabeth.

689
00:54:40,940 --> 00:54:42,780
You've done enough.

690
00:54:47,160 --> 00:54:49,280
To you and Dave for being here for this.

691
00:55:06,470 --> 00:55:09,800
Okay, Jimmy. I'll be back.

692
00:55:11,140 --> 00:55:14,060
I'll be by first thing tomorrow.
See you first thing.

693
00:55:14,220 --> 00:55:15,890
[JIMMY]
Good night.

694
00:55:16,850 --> 00:55:19,480
[CELESTE] Good night.
- Yeah, good night.

695
00:55:35,410 --> 00:55:38,040
[Phone Rings]

696
00:55:39,170 --> 00:55:40,580
Hello?

697
00:55:43,170 --> 00:55:47,380
Oh, Christ. Lauren, say something.

698
00:55:53,560 --> 00:55:56,350
"Okay. Hey, Sean, how was your day?"

699
00:55:57,060 --> 00:56:00,810
[SEAN] Oh, me? I'm tired of wishing
things made sense.

700
00:56:00,980 --> 00:56:03,230
I'm tired of caring about
some dead girl...

701
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:06,150
...and there's just gonna be
another one after her.

702
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:11,780
Sending killers to jail is sending them
where they've been heading all their lives.

703
00:56:11,950 --> 00:56:13,990
The dead are still dead.

704
00:56:16,620 --> 00:56:18,960
Jesus, I...

705
00:56:19,120 --> 00:56:21,250
...can't do this tonight.

706
00:56:21,540 --> 00:56:23,330
I just...

707
00:56:24,380 --> 00:56:26,170
I can't do it.

708
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:28,340
Bye, baby.

709
00:56:39,020 --> 00:56:40,640
[DAVE]
Because...

710
00:56:41,770 --> 00:56:45,270
...sometimes the man
wasn't a man at all.

711
00:56:45,480 --> 00:56:47,190
He was the boy.

712
00:56:48,110 --> 00:56:51,160
The boy who escaped from wolves.

713
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:54,830
An animal of the dusk.

714
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:56,990
Invisible.

715
00:56:57,410 --> 00:56:59,290
Silent.

716
00:56:59,870 --> 00:57:01,960
Living in a world...

717
00:57:02,130 --> 00:57:04,540
...the others never saw.

718
00:57:06,420 --> 00:57:08,920
World of fireflies.

719
00:57:10,510 --> 00:57:14,970
Unseen except as a flare
in the corner of your eye.

720
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:20,100
Vanished by the time
you turn your head toward it.

721
00:57:21,770 --> 00:57:23,980
[Wolf Howls]

722
00:57:31,660 --> 00:57:36,490
I just gotta get my head right.

723
00:57:39,460 --> 00:57:42,670
Catch a nice, long sleep.

724
00:57:43,130 --> 00:57:46,130
And the boy will go back to his forest.

725
00:57:48,210 --> 00:57:51,300
Back to his fireflies.

726
00:57:54,550 --> 00:57:57,220
[Footsteps Approaching]

727
00:57:58,850 --> 00:58:00,310
Is he asleep?

728
00:58:21,910 --> 00:58:24,330
How's Jimmy and everybody?

729
00:58:25,420 --> 00:58:27,130
Okay.

730
00:58:27,420 --> 00:58:29,170
It's weird.

731
00:58:29,630 --> 00:58:33,550
Took something like this for me and him
to become friends again.

732
00:58:33,720 --> 00:58:36,180
Dave? Dave.

733
00:58:39,430 --> 00:58:41,390
There's still nothing in the paper.

734
00:58:42,020 --> 00:58:45,980
About what?

735
00:58:48,690 --> 00:58:52,950
I don't know, honey. Maybe I didn't
hurt him as bad as I thought.

736
00:58:53,360 --> 00:58:55,990
He's a mugger. He's not going
to the hospital.

737
00:58:59,040 --> 00:59:00,700
Yeah.

738
00:59:00,870 --> 00:59:02,410
Right.

739
00:59:04,750 --> 00:59:07,340
Anyhow, it doesn't matter, does it?

740
00:59:08,130 --> 00:59:10,710
I mean, Katie Markum is dead.

741
00:59:11,880 --> 00:59:14,590
That seems more important right now.

742
00:59:43,750 --> 00:59:47,580
I know in my soul I contributed
to your death.

743
00:59:48,590 --> 00:59:51,090
But I don't know how.

744
01:00:10,940 --> 01:00:12,780
Brendan Harris aced his polygraph.

745
01:00:12,950 --> 01:00:15,610
Good. I didn't like him for it,
nor want him for it.

746
01:00:15,780 --> 01:00:17,120
Yeah. Poor fucking kid.

747
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:21,290
Ballistics will be back in a while.
Meantime, we got a list of bar patrons.

748
01:00:21,450 --> 01:00:24,120
All people who, I'm certain,
are dying to cooperate.

749
01:00:24,290 --> 01:00:27,040
Considering the crime, maybe.

750
01:00:27,290 --> 01:00:28,630
Dave Boyle?

751
01:00:28,790 --> 01:00:32,260
Hey, is that the guy you were friends
with as a kid? The car guy?

752
01:00:32,720 --> 01:00:33,970
Could be.

753
01:00:34,130 --> 01:00:37,640
He's a guy to talk to. He knows you.
He won't treat us like cops.

754
01:00:37,800 --> 01:00:41,510
- Clam up for no reason, huh?
- We'll see.

755
01:00:52,780 --> 01:00:54,400
[SEAN]
Hey, Boyle!

756
01:00:55,160 --> 01:00:57,530
- What's it been, seven, eight years?
- Yeah.

757
01:00:57,700 --> 01:00:59,200
Yeah. How you doing?

758
01:00:59,490 --> 01:01:00,830
This is my son, Michael.

759
01:01:00,990 --> 01:01:03,370
Hey, Michael. How you doing?
My name's Sean.

760
01:01:03,540 --> 01:01:04,870
I'm an old buddy of your dad's.

761
01:01:05,040 --> 01:01:06,420
- Hi.
[SEAN] Hi.

762
01:01:07,080 --> 01:01:10,340
- So you still with the staties?
- Homicide. This is my partner.

763
01:01:10,500 --> 01:01:13,210
- Sergeant Powers. How are you?
[SEAN] So you got a minute?

764
01:01:13,380 --> 01:01:17,680
- We'd love to ask some quick questions.
- I was gonna walk Michael to school.

765
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:21,760
- I can be back in a few minutes.
[SEAN] We'll walk with you, okay?

766
01:01:21,930 --> 01:01:23,430
Sure.

767
01:01:25,020 --> 01:01:26,810
So you look good.

768
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:30,350
- I hear rents are rising.
[DAVE] Yeah, the yuppies are coming.

769
01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:33,150
[SEAN] They're cutting my dad's
old house up into condos.

770
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:35,110
We walked by there the other day.

771
01:01:35,280 --> 01:01:37,530
Must be something we could do
to stop them.

772
01:01:37,700 --> 01:01:40,120
A friend of mine says the other day,
he says:

773
01:01:40,280 --> 01:01:42,410
"Neighborhood needs
a fucking crime wave.

774
01:01:42,580 --> 01:01:44,750
Get property values where they belong."

775
01:01:44,910 --> 01:01:49,420
Girls keep getting murdered up in
Pen Park you might get your wish.

776
01:01:49,580 --> 01:01:52,090
Dave. Call me Dave.

777
01:01:52,250 --> 01:01:54,210
You said the F-word, Dad.

778
01:01:54,590 --> 01:01:57,380
Yeah, I know.
Walk on up ahead, Michael.

779
01:01:57,550 --> 01:02:00,720
Us guys need to talk. Go on.

780
01:02:00,890 --> 01:02:04,890
- So, what's up, Sean?
- Yeah, you heard about Katie Markum?

781
01:02:05,060 --> 01:02:07,980
Yeah, I was at Jimmy's yesterday.
Celeste is there now.

782
01:02:08,140 --> 01:02:10,270
- Who's Celeste?
- My wife.

783
01:02:10,440 --> 01:02:14,690
- How's Jimmy doing?
- It's hard to tell. You know him.

784
01:02:14,860 --> 01:02:18,240
- Yeah, so the reason we came by...
- Listen, I saw her.

785
01:02:19,030 --> 01:02:23,450
Katie. I don't know if you know that.
At McGill's, the night she died.

786
01:02:23,620 --> 01:02:25,620
That's what we wanted to talk about.

787
01:02:25,790 --> 01:02:29,750
They were at a couple of bars that night.
Your name turned up for McGill's.

788
01:02:29,920 --> 01:02:32,210
They put on quite a show
dancing on the bar.

789
01:02:32,380 --> 01:02:35,920
- Pretty drunk, huh?
- But it was harmless.

790
01:02:36,090 --> 01:02:39,130
They weren't stripping or nothing.
They were just 19.

791
01:02:39,300 --> 01:02:40,890
What time did they leave?

792
01:02:41,050 --> 01:02:44,100
I left at 1. They must've left
15 minutes before me.

793
01:02:44,270 --> 01:02:47,390
- So we'll say 12:45?
- Sounds about right.

794
01:02:48,440 --> 01:02:51,060
[SEAN] You see anything unusual
or anyone...?

795
01:02:51,230 --> 01:02:52,900
[DAVE]
Michael.

796
01:02:53,400 --> 01:02:55,110
[SEAN] Like what?
I don't know.

797
01:02:55,280 --> 01:02:56,610
A guy watching the girls?

798
01:02:56,780 --> 01:02:59,610
A guy with hate in his eyes?
A woman-hater?

799
01:03:00,950 --> 01:03:05,620
No, if they hadn't danced on the bar,
it would've been business as usual.

800
01:03:05,790 --> 01:03:07,160
See you later, Dad.

801
01:03:07,330 --> 01:03:09,120
- You got your milk money?
- Uh-huh.

802
01:03:16,130 --> 01:03:18,130
Fuck, I hated school.

803
01:03:18,630 --> 01:03:20,180
What?

804
01:03:20,390 --> 01:03:21,430
Oh, uh...

805
01:03:21,600 --> 01:03:24,680
Yeah, me too, Sean.

806
01:03:24,890 --> 01:03:30,350
Uh, just one more thing, Mr. Boyle.
Where did you go after you left McGill's?

807
01:03:30,520 --> 01:03:33,650
- Home.
- Home by 1:15, would you say?

808
01:03:33,820 --> 01:03:36,610
- Roughly. Sure.
- All right.

809
01:03:38,320 --> 01:03:41,360
Yeah, well, thanks a lot, Dave.
We'll grab a beer sometime?

810
01:03:41,820 --> 01:03:44,990
- Yeah, I'd like that, Sean.
[SEAN] All right.

811
01:03:46,910 --> 01:03:49,370
[Bell Rings]

812
01:03:51,670 --> 01:03:53,250
What?

813
01:03:53,630 --> 01:03:56,000
[WHITEY]
What happened to him in that car?

814
01:04:03,350 --> 01:04:05,180
Can you believe this?

815
01:04:05,350 --> 01:04:08,350
Man, it's the same as Dunkin' Donuts.
It costs 15 times the price.

816
01:04:08,520 --> 01:04:10,310
Yeah, well...

817
01:04:10,940 --> 01:04:14,400
You know, you take away love,
money or hate as motives...

818
01:04:14,570 --> 01:04:16,480
...you're not left with a whole lot.

819
01:04:16,650 --> 01:04:19,240
Well, if this Markum thing's random,
I mean, shit.

820
01:04:19,400 --> 01:04:23,620
Yeah, tell me about it. But the old lady,
Prior, she doesn't hear a scream.

821
01:04:23,780 --> 01:04:25,740
Hears a gunshot,
before that a "hi"...

822
01:04:25,910 --> 01:04:29,160
...which tells me the girl is either
friendly or she knew him.

823
01:04:29,330 --> 01:04:33,960
She turns to the curb, not too fast or she
hops it. Foot's off the clutch. She stalls.

824
01:04:34,130 --> 01:04:38,000
- She says, "Hi." He shoots her.
- She slams the door into him, takes off.

825
01:04:38,170 --> 01:04:40,840
What makes her swerve
without hitting the brakes?

826
01:04:41,010 --> 01:04:43,640
- I don't know. Something in the street.
- Maybe.

827
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:47,060
This Markum girl couldn't have
weighed more than what, 110?

828
01:04:47,220 --> 01:04:51,520
- Hits hard enough to get a jump on him?
- Maybe he's knocked back on his heels.

829
01:04:51,690 --> 01:04:55,230
Your pal Dave strikes me as a guy
permanently back on his heels.

830
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:58,610
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait a second, how
did we get to Dave Boyle all of a sudden?

831
01:04:58,780 --> 01:05:01,490
[WHITEY] We just got to him.
- He's a guy who was in the bar.

832
01:05:01,660 --> 01:05:04,490
The last place, Seany,
the last place she was at.

833
01:05:04,660 --> 01:05:06,780
The guy is wrong. You saw his hand.

834
01:05:06,950 --> 01:05:10,620
Yeah, I saw his hand. You seriously
want to take a look at Dave Boyle?

835
01:05:10,790 --> 01:05:12,960
Just a little one.

836
01:05:17,960 --> 01:05:22,220
I'd recommend two sets of
visiting hours, from 3 to 5, and 7 to 9.

837
01:05:22,380 --> 01:05:24,550
- Sure.
- Good.

838
01:05:26,100 --> 01:05:30,890
- Have you thought about flowers?
- I'll call Knopfler's this afternoon.

839
01:05:31,230 --> 01:05:32,560
Good.

840
01:05:37,940 --> 01:05:39,860
And the notice?

841
01:05:40,700 --> 01:05:42,070
Notice?

842
01:05:43,450 --> 01:05:48,330
Yes, the obituary. We can take care of it
if you give us her basic information.

843
01:05:48,490 --> 01:05:51,080
Or if you prefer donations
in lieu of flowers?

844
01:05:51,250 --> 01:05:52,960
Where's my daughter?

845
01:05:55,460 --> 01:05:57,500
Downstairs, in the basement.

846
01:05:58,340 --> 01:05:59,630
I wanna see her.

847
01:06:47,010 --> 01:06:49,350
I'm gonna find him, Katie.

848
01:06:50,770 --> 01:06:53,850
I'm gonna find him before the police do.

849
01:06:54,230 --> 01:06:56,850
I'm gonna find the man,
and I'm gonna kill him.

850
01:07:00,780 --> 01:07:03,360
[MAN]
Did you say something, Mr. Markum?

851
01:07:06,820 --> 01:07:08,740
The notice.

852
01:07:10,040 --> 01:07:12,410
It should read; "Katherine Markum...

853
01:07:14,080 --> 01:07:17,580
...beloved daughter
of James and Marita, deceased...

854
01:07:18,340 --> 01:07:22,590
...stepdaughter of Annabeth, sister to..."

855
01:07:22,920 --> 01:07:26,380
"Sister to Sara and Nadine."

856
01:08:06,760 --> 01:08:10,800
[DAVE] You guys again?
- Yeah. We're like two bad pennies.

857
01:08:11,760 --> 01:08:14,060
- You dropping in on Jimmy?
- Yeah.

858
01:08:14,230 --> 01:08:16,980
Do you have some kind of, what,
break in the case?

859
01:08:17,150 --> 01:08:20,150
No, just paying our respects.
Where you off to?

860
01:08:20,320 --> 01:08:22,940
[DAVE]
Annabeth got a craving for cigarettes.

861
01:08:23,150 --> 01:08:24,940
I'm gonna go get some.
See you in a minute.

862
01:08:25,110 --> 01:08:28,950
By the way, Mr. Boyle, what happened
to your hand there?

863
01:08:29,570 --> 01:08:35,410
Uh, garbage disposal. It jammed,
I stuck my hand in, it started again.

864
01:08:35,580 --> 01:08:37,290
- Stupid.
[WHITEY] Yeah, painful.

865
01:08:41,630 --> 01:08:43,960
Garbage disposal. Bullshit.

866
01:08:44,130 --> 01:08:48,130
Yeah. Well, it doesn't mean
he killed anybody either. Come on.

867
01:08:51,390 --> 01:08:53,640
[Knocking]

868
01:09:01,730 --> 01:09:04,780
- Heard you could use one.
- Thanks.

869
01:09:06,150 --> 01:09:10,490
- I quit 10 years ago, you believe this?
- Whatever you need right now.

870
01:09:12,200 --> 01:09:14,200
Come on in, I'll get Jimmy.

871
01:09:19,420 --> 01:09:22,540
I got a couple errands I gotta run.
I'll be back in an hour.

872
01:09:22,710 --> 01:09:25,380
You don't have to come back, Celeste.
I'll be fine.

873
01:09:25,550 --> 01:09:26,720
[CELESTE] Sure?
- Celeste Boyle?

874
01:09:26,880 --> 01:09:28,340
Uh, yeah.

875
01:09:28,510 --> 01:09:31,930
I'm Sean Devine, an old friend of Dave's.
This is Whitey Powers.

876
01:09:32,100 --> 01:09:35,140
- Mrs. Boyle.
- Nice to meet you.

877
01:09:35,310 --> 01:09:36,810
Look, I gotta go.

878
01:09:39,690 --> 01:09:41,480
- Oh, damn it.
[WHITEY] What?

879
01:09:41,650 --> 01:09:43,400
I left my report pad in the cruiser.

880
01:09:43,570 --> 01:09:46,150
- You better go get it.
- Yeah.

881
01:09:46,990 --> 01:09:48,450
Come on.

882
01:09:53,540 --> 01:09:57,040
Hey, Celeste, could I ask you
a quick question?

883
01:09:57,580 --> 01:10:00,000
- Me?
- What time did Dave get home Saturday?

884
01:10:00,170 --> 01:10:01,790
- What?
- It's a little thing.

885
01:10:01,960 --> 01:10:05,710
We're running a time line on everything
involving Katie. I'm sure...

886
01:10:05,880 --> 01:10:07,920
...Dave told you he saw her
at McGill's.

887
01:10:09,510 --> 01:10:11,680
You think Dave killed Katie?

888
01:10:12,140 --> 01:10:15,390
Oh, no. God. I didn't say that.
Why would I even think that?

889
01:10:17,810 --> 01:10:21,230
- I don't know.
- No. It's just that we could figure out...

890
01:10:21,400 --> 01:10:24,980
...what time she was on the road
if we knew what time Dave got home.

891
01:10:25,150 --> 01:10:28,320
See, it's 5 minutes from your place
to McGill's...

892
01:10:28,490 --> 01:10:31,950
...and Katie left 15 minutes
before Dave did. You see what I mean.

893
01:10:32,410 --> 01:10:35,450
- I was asleep.
- Huh?

894
01:10:36,580 --> 01:10:41,790
Saturday night, when Dave came in,
I was asleep.

895
01:10:41,960 --> 01:10:44,290
Okay. Well, thanks.

896
01:10:55,020 --> 01:10:56,770
Bullshit.

897
01:10:56,930 --> 01:10:58,430
[SEAN]
No, he was dating Katie, Jim.

898
01:10:58,600 --> 01:11:02,270
They were gonna elope to Vegas.
We found tickets under their names.

899
01:11:02,440 --> 01:11:04,150
Brendan Harris confirmed it.

900
01:11:04,690 --> 01:11:05,940
Remember what you said?

901
01:11:06,440 --> 01:11:10,950
How she looked at you on Saturday like
she was preparing to never see you again?

902
01:11:12,570 --> 01:11:16,410
- Did Brendan Harris kill my daughter?
- No.

903
01:11:16,580 --> 01:11:18,160
You're 100 percent sure?

904
01:11:18,830 --> 01:11:23,130
Passed his poly with flying colors, plus it
seemed to me like he really loved her.

905
01:11:26,130 --> 01:11:29,050
Jimmy, I'm just curious, man.

906
01:11:29,220 --> 01:11:31,630
Why are you so dead set
against that kid?

907
01:11:31,800 --> 01:11:35,470
He said Katie told him you'd disown
her if she ever dated a Harris.

908
01:11:37,140 --> 01:11:40,310
I knew his father. They called him
"Just Ray" Harris.

909
01:11:40,480 --> 01:11:41,810
Why is that?

910
01:11:43,860 --> 01:11:46,480
There were so many Rays
in the neighborhood.

911
01:11:46,650 --> 01:11:50,820
You had "Crazy Ray" Bucheck,
"Psycho Ray" Dorian.

912
01:11:51,820 --> 01:11:54,990
The cool names were taken,
so he got stuck with "Just Ray."

913
01:11:55,160 --> 01:11:57,990
We never got along.
I flat out didn't like him.

914
01:11:58,830 --> 01:12:03,670
And he cut out on his wife when she was
pregnant with that little mute of hers.

915
01:12:04,080 --> 01:12:05,840
I don't know.

916
01:12:06,170 --> 01:12:09,000
I just figure the apple doesn't fall
far from the tree.

917
01:12:09,300 --> 01:12:14,340
I didn't want Brendan or any other Harris
dating Katie or any daughter of mine.

918
01:12:16,510 --> 01:12:19,310
I can't believe we're talking about
Just Ray Harris.

919
01:12:19,470 --> 01:12:22,020
How about this? We've interviewed
witnesses...

920
01:12:22,190 --> 01:12:24,350
...canvassed people
who were in the bar.

921
01:12:24,520 --> 01:12:28,520
We've run into more than a few of them
who were questioned...

922
01:12:28,690 --> 01:12:32,200
...before us by one or more
of the Savage brothers.

923
01:12:32,360 --> 01:12:35,660
- So?
- So the Savages are not policemen, Jim.

924
01:12:35,830 --> 01:12:39,580
- Some people don't talk to policemen.
- With all due respect...

925
01:12:39,750 --> 01:12:42,250
...and just so we're clear,
this is our case.

926
01:12:43,000 --> 01:12:45,420
- How long?
- How long what?

927
01:12:45,750 --> 01:12:48,210
How long before you catch
my daughter's killer?

928
01:12:48,380 --> 01:12:49,710
You bargaining with us?

929
01:12:51,550 --> 01:12:52,840
Bargaining?

930
01:12:54,550 --> 01:12:56,390
You giving us a deadline?

931
01:12:59,390 --> 01:13:03,230
We'll speak for Katie, Mr. Markum.
If that's okay with you.

932
01:13:04,480 --> 01:13:08,980
Just find my daughter's killer, sergeant.
I'm not standing in your way.

933
01:13:12,780 --> 01:13:16,740
The last thing we need is Markum and
the Savages putting the fear of God...

934
01:13:16,910 --> 01:13:19,950
...into the neighborhood.
- We grew up terrified of those brothers.

935
01:13:20,120 --> 01:13:23,750
Eleven months apart, like their mother
ran a loose-cannon factory.

936
01:13:23,920 --> 01:13:26,380
Fucking knuckleheads.

937
01:13:29,420 --> 01:13:31,510
Ballistics are in on the Markum murder.

938
01:13:31,670 --> 01:13:35,050
- Yeah, you got a match?
- Mm-hm. You're gonna love it.

939
01:13:36,220 --> 01:13:39,600
[MAN] It's a perfect match.
Gun was a.38 Smith.

940
01:13:39,770 --> 01:13:44,060
Part of a lot stolen from a gun dealer
in New Hampshire in 1982.

941
01:13:44,230 --> 01:13:49,360
The gun that killed Katherine Markum
was used in a liquor-store holdup in 1984.

942
01:13:49,530 --> 01:13:50,900
- In Buckingham.
- The Flats?

943
01:13:51,070 --> 01:13:55,700
Rome Basin. Place called Looney Liquors.
I pulled the file.

944
01:13:55,860 --> 01:13:59,950
It was a two-man job.
They fired a warning shot into a wall.

945
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:03,750
- That's where the bullet got pulled.
- Nice work.

946
01:14:03,920 --> 01:14:06,080
Thought you'd like that.

947
01:14:06,880 --> 01:14:10,380
[Thunder Crashing]

948
01:14:26,150 --> 01:14:29,440
[Door Opens And Closes]

949
01:14:35,780 --> 01:14:37,700
It's okay, Ray.

950
01:14:38,490 --> 01:14:40,330
Don't worry about it.

951
01:14:54,340 --> 01:14:55,680
Ma said that?

952
01:14:58,260 --> 01:14:59,510
That I'm better off?

953
01:15:05,390 --> 01:15:08,350
I loved her! You know what that's like?

954
01:15:08,770 --> 01:15:10,020
Huh?

955
01:15:15,200 --> 01:15:17,030
I'm sorry.

956
01:15:25,120 --> 01:15:26,960
No, you're wrong.

957
01:15:28,130 --> 01:15:30,380
I won't ever feel that again.

958
01:15:31,170 --> 01:15:36,340
Right there. Went in through a bottle
of Jack and stuck in the wall right there.

959
01:15:36,510 --> 01:15:40,390
[SEAN] Scary, huh?
- Scarier than a glass of milk, right?

960
01:15:40,560 --> 01:15:43,100
So take me through it.
These two guys come in...

961
01:15:43,310 --> 01:15:47,140
In rubber masks.
They came in through here.

962
01:15:49,480 --> 01:15:52,020
- That's the storeroom.
[SEAN] Uh-huh.

963
01:15:53,030 --> 01:15:56,740
There's a door back there
that leads to a loading dock.

964
01:15:57,030 --> 01:15:59,240
I always keep that door locked.

965
01:15:59,950 --> 01:16:02,910
So they must have had a key.

966
01:16:03,080 --> 01:16:07,080
A key? So, what you're saying
is that it was an inside job?

967
01:16:07,250 --> 01:16:11,540
It had to be. One of them, at least,
worked for me at some point.

968
01:16:11,710 --> 01:16:16,420
The only reason they fired that warning
shot was they must have known...

969
01:16:16,840 --> 01:16:18,590
...I kept this under the counter.

970
01:16:18,760 --> 01:16:22,390
- And you told the police that at the time.
- Yeah.

971
01:16:23,310 --> 01:16:25,850
Sure, they went through
my employment records.

972
01:16:26,020 --> 01:16:28,600
Questioned everybody
who used to work for me.

973
01:16:28,770 --> 01:16:31,860
- Never made an arrest.
- Still have a copy of those records?

974
01:16:32,020 --> 01:16:36,950
Yeah, it's in a box in the office there.
But I know who did it.

975
01:16:37,110 --> 01:16:38,610
Oh, yeah?

976
01:16:38,780 --> 01:16:41,490
- This guy I fired a couple of weeks before.
[SEAN] Mm-hm.

977
01:16:41,660 --> 01:16:45,580
Son of a bitch came in here
a few days after the robbery.

978
01:16:45,750 --> 01:16:49,960
He had this fucking goddamn grin
on his face.

979
01:16:50,130 --> 01:16:52,210
And I just knew.

980
01:16:52,380 --> 01:16:55,130
Go tell a grin to a jury, right?

981
01:16:55,800 --> 01:16:57,630
You remember his name?

982
01:16:58,630 --> 01:17:00,590
Do I look senile to you?

983
01:17:00,970 --> 01:17:03,260
- No, sir.
- Name...

984
01:17:03,470 --> 01:17:05,470
...was Ray Harris.

985
01:17:05,850 --> 01:17:08,890
We used to call him "Just Ray."

986
01:17:11,650 --> 01:17:14,690
You say they used the same gun
for another crime?

987
01:17:15,690 --> 01:17:19,400
- That's correct, sir.
- Thanks for your help, Mr. Looney.

988
01:17:23,950 --> 01:17:26,410
[Door Unlocks]

989
01:17:31,330 --> 01:17:33,210
[DAVE]
Where you been?

990
01:17:34,500 --> 01:17:36,210
[CELESTE]
Out.

991
01:17:36,420 --> 01:17:39,130
[TV Playing]

992
01:17:39,470 --> 01:17:41,470
What you watching?

993
01:17:41,640 --> 01:17:43,720
[DAVE]
Some vampire movie.

994
01:17:44,430 --> 01:17:47,020
Guy just got his head torn off.

995
01:17:48,770 --> 01:17:50,940
Where'd you go, Celeste?

996
01:17:55,270 --> 01:17:57,530
[CELESTE]
I was sitting in my car...

997
01:17:57,990 --> 01:18:01,160
...down by the channel.
You know...

998
01:18:01,780 --> 01:18:03,200
...thinking about things.

999
01:18:05,040 --> 01:18:08,410
- What'd you think about?
- Oh, you know...

1000
01:18:08,830 --> 01:18:11,830
No, actually, I don't know.

1001
01:18:17,550 --> 01:18:20,880
Things. You know, the day.

1002
01:18:22,510 --> 01:18:25,350
About Katie being dead.

1003
01:18:25,930 --> 01:18:28,770
And poor Annabeth and Jimmy,
you know...

1004
01:18:29,480 --> 01:18:31,350
...those things.

1005
01:18:31,730 --> 01:18:33,730
Those things.

1006
01:18:34,520 --> 01:18:36,940
Know what I was thinking about, huh?

1007
01:18:38,570 --> 01:18:40,110
Vampires.

1008
01:18:41,820 --> 01:18:43,070
What about them?

1009
01:18:44,950 --> 01:18:48,080
They're undead...

1010
01:18:48,250 --> 01:18:51,330
...but I think maybe there's
something beautiful about it.

1011
01:18:51,500 --> 01:18:55,040
Maybe one day you wake up
and you forget what it's like...

1012
01:18:55,210 --> 01:18:57,090
...to be human.
Maybe then it's okay.

1013
01:18:58,510 --> 01:19:00,760
What the fuck you talking about, Dave?

1014
01:19:01,090 --> 01:19:03,470
Vampires, sweetie. Werewolves.

1015
01:19:03,640 --> 01:19:05,760
You're not making any sense.

1016
01:19:08,810 --> 01:19:10,560
You think I killed Katie?

1017
01:19:10,730 --> 01:19:12,850
- Celeste.
- What...?

1018
01:19:13,060 --> 01:19:17,270
- That the sense we're making these days?
- Where'd you come up with that?

1019
01:19:17,440 --> 01:19:20,820
You've barely looked at me since you
found out Katie was dead.

1020
01:19:20,990 --> 01:19:22,740
In fact, you seem repulsed by me.

1021
01:19:22,910 --> 01:19:24,660
- Dave!
- What?

1022
01:19:24,820 --> 01:19:29,580
I don't think anything.
I'm confused, okay?

1023
01:19:29,750 --> 01:19:31,540
Even your friend Sean
asked about...

1024
01:19:31,710 --> 01:19:33,790
He's not my friend, if you didn't know.

1025
01:19:33,960 --> 01:19:38,630
He asked me about you.
What time you came home.

1026
01:19:39,300 --> 01:19:42,590
- What'd you tell him?
- I said I was asleep.

1027
01:19:43,590 --> 01:19:46,720
- That's good thinking, baby.
- Jesus Christ, Dave!

1028
01:19:46,890 --> 01:19:49,810
- Why not tell them about the mugger?
- The mugger?

1029
01:19:49,980 --> 01:19:52,600
The mugger! I see how
your mind's working. I do.

1030
01:19:52,770 --> 01:19:55,980
I come home with blood on me
the same night Katie's murdered.

1031
01:19:56,150 --> 01:19:57,820
I must have killed her, right?

1032
01:19:58,230 --> 01:19:59,940
Fuck!

1033
01:20:02,820 --> 01:20:05,280
[Laughing And Sniffling]

1034
01:20:27,720 --> 01:20:29,220
Henry...

1035
01:20:29,850 --> 01:20:32,350
What? Henry?

1036
01:20:34,650 --> 01:20:37,110
Henry and George.

1037
01:20:40,820 --> 01:20:43,030
I never told anyone that before.

1038
01:20:44,910 --> 01:20:46,370
Those were their names.

1039
01:20:47,950 --> 01:20:50,540
Isn't that fucking hilarious?

1040
01:20:53,710 --> 01:20:56,710
At least that's what they called
themselves, but...

1041
01:20:57,880 --> 01:21:01,420
...they were wolves, and Dave...

1042
01:21:02,090 --> 01:21:06,140
...was the boy who escaped
from wolves.

1043
01:21:08,350 --> 01:21:10,520
What are you talking about, Dave?

1044
01:21:11,060 --> 01:21:13,430
I'm talking Henry and George.

1045
01:21:14,440 --> 01:21:17,230
They took me on a four-day ride.

1046
01:21:17,940 --> 01:21:23,280
They buried me in this ratty old cellar
with a sleeping bag.

1047
01:21:24,110 --> 01:21:27,030
And, man, Celeste...

1048
01:21:27,240 --> 01:21:28,950
...did they have their fun.

1049
01:21:30,910 --> 01:21:34,290
And no one came to help old Dave then.

1050
01:21:36,290 --> 01:21:41,090
Dave had to pretend to be
somebody else.

1051
01:21:46,090 --> 01:21:48,720
You mean, all those years ago...

1052
01:21:51,600 --> 01:21:54,020
...when you were a little boy?

1053
01:21:55,690 --> 01:21:57,310
Dave...

1054
01:21:57,480 --> 01:21:59,570
Dave's dead.

1055
01:22:00,940 --> 01:22:05,070
I don't know who came out of that
cellar, but it sure as shit wasn't Dave!

1056
01:22:06,450 --> 01:22:07,870
You see, honey...

1057
01:22:08,030 --> 01:22:09,530
Fuck!

1058
01:22:09,780 --> 01:22:12,410
It's like vampires.

1059
01:22:15,460 --> 01:22:17,460
Once it's in you...

1060
01:22:18,880 --> 01:22:20,790
...it stays.

1061
01:22:22,170 --> 01:22:24,210
What stays?

1062
01:22:30,890 --> 01:22:34,100
Did you know there were
child prostitutes in Rome Basin?

1063
01:22:34,980 --> 01:22:36,430
What?

1064
01:22:42,230 --> 01:22:43,730
Fuck!

1065
01:22:46,990 --> 01:22:49,990
I can't trust my mind anymore, Celeste.

1066
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:52,160
I'm warning you...

1067
01:22:54,000 --> 01:22:55,830
...I can't trust my mind.

1068
01:22:58,790 --> 01:23:02,210
I gotta go out,
try to get my head around it.

1069
01:23:02,380 --> 01:23:04,210
[Door Closes]

1070
01:23:04,550 --> 01:23:13,970
Okay.

1071
01:23:15,680 --> 01:23:19,560
- The gun sends us in a different direction.
- I don't see it that way.

1072
01:23:19,730 --> 01:23:22,310
What does Just Ray's gun
have to do with Dave?

1073
01:23:22,480 --> 01:23:24,270
These things get passed around.

1074
01:23:24,440 --> 01:23:27,400
Just Ray may have blown town,
but his gun never did.

1075
01:23:27,570 --> 01:23:30,490
I say we talk with Brendan Harris
in the morning.

1076
01:23:30,660 --> 01:23:34,740
And I say Dave Boyle. The hand story.
The wife, she's definitely scared.

1077
01:23:34,910 --> 01:23:39,370
They're hiding something, but Boyle's
as much a killer as Brendan Harris.

1078
01:23:39,540 --> 01:23:43,710
Boyle fits the profile, a fucking T.
Mid-30s, white, marginally employed...

1079
01:23:43,880 --> 01:23:48,050
...sexually abused as a kid. On paper,
this guy should be in jail already.

1080
01:23:48,220 --> 01:23:50,550
Katie Markum
was not sexually abused, see?

1081
01:23:50,720 --> 01:23:54,100
In that equation,
sexual emission is part of the deal.

1082
01:23:54,270 --> 01:23:58,270
You were friends when you were kids.
This makes you a fucking liability.

1083
01:23:58,440 --> 01:23:59,730
Hey, he's not my friend.

1084
01:23:59,900 --> 01:24:04,400
Turns out you're right, I'll have my cuffs
off my hip faster than yours.

1085
01:24:19,000 --> 01:24:20,620
Hey, Jimmy.

1086
01:24:21,880 --> 01:24:23,420
You're out late.

1087
01:24:23,590 --> 01:24:25,300
Yeah, you too.

1088
01:24:26,760 --> 01:24:28,550
It's cold, huh?

1089
01:24:28,800 --> 01:24:31,050
Yeah, I guess.

1090
01:24:38,520 --> 01:24:40,100
You know, I...

1091
01:24:40,600 --> 01:24:42,650
I been sitting out here...

1092
01:24:42,810 --> 01:24:44,940
...over the last few years...

1093
01:24:46,860 --> 01:24:50,950
...waiting on Katie to get back
from someplace.

1094
01:24:51,950 --> 01:24:56,950
About midnight, I'd say to Annabeth,
"I'm gonna sit on the porch for a while."

1095
01:25:01,500 --> 01:25:03,340
Weird thing is...

1096
01:25:04,210 --> 01:25:06,300
...it seemed to bring her back.

1097
01:25:10,800 --> 01:25:12,840
I saw her, you know.

1098
01:25:14,680 --> 01:25:16,350
Saw who?

1099
01:25:16,600 --> 01:25:19,680
Katie. I was at McGill's Saturday night.

1100
01:25:21,690 --> 01:25:25,820
- You saw Katie Saturday night?
- Never got around to telling you.

1101
01:25:28,820 --> 01:25:30,490
Did you talk to her?

1102
01:25:31,320 --> 01:25:33,820
Just nodded hello at one point.

1103
01:25:34,660 --> 01:25:37,160
Next time I looked up, she was gone.

1104
01:25:43,380 --> 01:25:44,880
But, uh...

1105
01:25:45,040 --> 01:25:46,630
...Jimmy...

1106
01:25:48,090 --> 01:25:50,010
...she looked, um...

1107
01:25:51,340 --> 01:25:52,840
...happy.

1108
01:26:08,990 --> 01:26:13,030
Uh, I got more walking to do.
Good night.

1109
01:26:24,920 --> 01:26:28,170
- You stole his car.
- His car was officially towed.

1110
01:26:28,340 --> 01:26:32,170
[SEAN] From the front of his house.
- No! It was abandoned in Rome Basin...

1111
01:26:32,340 --> 01:26:33,840
...adjacent to the parkway.

1112
01:26:34,010 --> 01:26:38,560
Lucky for us, the parkway's state
jurisdiction. Some kids jacked the car...

1113
01:26:38,730 --> 01:26:42,310
...they took it for a joy ride...
- What? Why'd you do it?

1114
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:47,400
After I left last night, I decided to talk
to Boyle myself, put some fear into him.

1115
01:26:47,570 --> 01:26:52,360
I get to his house, I decide to look in
his car, see what he's got. I find blood.

1116
01:26:52,530 --> 01:26:55,240
- Blood?
- Front seat of Dave's car. B-negative.

1117
01:26:55,410 --> 01:26:59,240
- How much?
- A bit. Found more in the trunk. A lot.

1118
01:26:59,410 --> 01:27:02,250
Type O, same type as Katie Markum.

1119
01:27:02,420 --> 01:27:05,170
Wait, Katie Markum
never got in anybody's trunk.

1120
01:27:05,340 --> 01:27:08,090
She was chased through the park
where she died.

1121
01:27:08,250 --> 01:27:12,090
- It's enough to ask questions.
- Your search is gonna get tossed out.

1122
01:27:12,260 --> 01:27:17,140
No, found and abandoned in state
jurisdiction, for insurance purposes.

1123
01:27:17,310 --> 01:27:21,430
- In the best interest of the owner.
- Get a physical search, file the report.

1124
01:27:21,600 --> 01:27:23,100
[WHITEY]
Bingo.

1125
01:27:23,770 --> 01:27:26,440
So, you wanna talk to him,
or should I send him home?

1126
01:27:26,770 --> 01:27:29,780
- Dave's here?
- I've had him in the box for an hour.

1127
01:27:29,940 --> 01:27:33,070
Sent two of my biggest, ugliest troopers
to pick him up.

1128
01:27:34,870 --> 01:27:36,120
Come on, Mr. Boyle!

1129
01:27:36,280 --> 01:27:39,490
We know you didn't get that swollen
hand sticking it in the garbage disposal.

1130
01:27:40,120 --> 01:27:44,920
- Oh, yeah? How do you know that?
- Why's your wife afraid of you?

1131
01:27:45,460 --> 01:27:47,960
She know what really happened
to your hand?

1132
01:27:54,260 --> 01:27:57,140
How about a Sprite or something?

1133
01:27:57,300 --> 01:28:01,350
How about you tell us what really
happened Saturday night, Mr. Boyle?

1134
01:28:01,520 --> 01:28:03,060
You lied.

1135
01:28:03,230 --> 01:28:05,770
That's your opinion,
which you're entitled to.

1136
01:28:05,940 --> 01:28:10,820
- Hey, you think this is funny?
- No, I don't. I'm tired, I'm hung-over.

1137
01:28:10,980 --> 01:28:15,450
Not only was my car stolen last night,
but now you won't release it to me.

1138
01:28:15,610 --> 01:28:17,200
Okay.

1139
01:28:18,700 --> 01:28:20,370
All right.

1140
01:28:20,830 --> 01:28:24,000
Tell us, Mr. Boyle,
how did you get the blood in your car?

1141
01:28:24,160 --> 01:28:26,830
- What blood?
- Let's start with the front seat.

1142
01:28:28,750 --> 01:28:30,750
What are you looking at him for?

1143
01:28:32,210 --> 01:28:35,880
Hey, you think I could get
that Sprite, Sean?

1144
01:28:36,680 --> 01:28:38,180
Sure.

1145
01:28:38,470 --> 01:28:40,470
[DAVE]
Oh, I get it.

1146
01:28:41,100 --> 01:28:42,930
You're the good cop.

1147
01:28:43,430 --> 01:28:46,480
How about a meatball sub
while you're at it?

1148
01:28:46,690 --> 01:28:49,860
I ain't your bitch, Dave.
Looks like you'll have to wait.

1149
01:28:50,980 --> 01:28:54,240
Yeah, but you're someone's bitch,
aren't you, Sean?

1150
01:28:56,410 --> 01:28:59,910
The blood on your front seat, Dave.
Answer the sergeant.

1151
01:29:02,660 --> 01:29:05,790
We got a chainlink fence
in our back yard.

1152
01:29:05,960 --> 01:29:09,170
Me and my kid play Wiffle Ball
every afternoon after school.

1153
01:29:09,790 --> 01:29:13,960
He's getting good, so most of the balls
are on the other side of the fence.

1154
01:29:14,130 --> 01:29:16,800
So I climb it.
Except I slip...

1155
01:29:16,970 --> 01:29:20,180
...slice myself where the links curl in,
right here.

1156
01:29:20,350 --> 01:29:22,140
Bled like hell.

1157
01:29:22,560 --> 01:29:25,810
Ten minutes later,
I gotta pick up Michael at school.

1158
01:29:26,390 --> 01:29:29,560
Probably was still bleeding
when I got in the front seat.

1159
01:29:29,730 --> 01:29:31,440
What blood type are you?

1160
01:29:32,110 --> 01:29:33,780
B-negative.

1161
01:29:34,030 --> 01:29:36,740
Yeah? That's the match we got.

1162
01:29:37,320 --> 01:29:39,410
- Well, there you go.
- Not quite.

1163
01:29:39,570 --> 01:29:42,080
Blood in the trunk of the car
wasn't B-negative.

1164
01:29:43,410 --> 01:29:46,250
I don't know anything
about any blood in the trunk.

1165
01:29:46,920 --> 01:29:50,080
No idea how half a pint of blood
got in the trunk?

1166
01:29:50,250 --> 01:29:53,420
- None.
- This is not the way you wanna go.

1167
01:29:53,590 --> 01:29:55,300
[WHITEY]
How will that look in court?

1168
01:29:55,470 --> 01:29:59,390
You not knowing how someone else's
blood got in the trunk of your car?

1169
01:29:59,550 --> 01:30:02,470
Gonna look fine, I suppose.
You filed the report.

1170
01:30:02,970 --> 01:30:04,770
What report?

1171
01:30:05,140 --> 01:30:09,440
The stolen-car report. The car
wasn't in my possession last night.

1172
01:30:09,770 --> 01:30:12,860
So whatever the thieves used it for,
you should find out...

1173
01:30:13,030 --> 01:30:15,610
...because it sounds like they
were up to no good.

1174
01:30:21,620 --> 01:30:25,120
Things looking any better
on the Sprite, Sean?

1175
01:30:25,370 --> 01:30:28,920
Well, you just got too fucking smart.
The car is inadmissible.

1176
01:30:29,080 --> 01:30:31,750
Anything there, his lawyers say
was put by thieves.

1177
01:30:31,920 --> 01:30:34,510
- I can break him.
- He just kicked our asses!

1178
01:30:34,670 --> 01:30:36,840
You still think Dave
wouldn't hurt a fly...

1179
01:30:37,010 --> 01:30:39,300
- Is that the point? No.
- What is the point?

1180
01:30:39,470 --> 01:30:43,470
We can break this open on the gun.
It's the gun.

1181
01:30:43,810 --> 01:30:46,140
Okay. Maybe.

1182
01:30:48,650 --> 01:30:50,310
So, what do we do with Dave?

1183
01:30:51,980 --> 01:30:53,520
Fuck it. Kick him loose.

1184
01:30:54,400 --> 01:30:58,320
Maybe a Celtic cross.
That's always a popular choice.

1185
01:30:58,530 --> 01:31:01,820
Or this lovely red marble here.

1186
01:31:02,660 --> 01:31:04,490
Or a figural.

1187
01:31:04,660 --> 01:31:06,250
That one.

1188
01:31:06,750 --> 01:31:10,250
Very good. Nice and simple.

1189
01:31:18,720 --> 01:31:20,340
Hey, Jimmy!

1190
01:31:23,760 --> 01:31:25,930
Annabeth said you were here.

1191
01:31:27,270 --> 01:31:29,390
We been asking around, like you said to.

1192
01:31:29,560 --> 01:31:31,100
- Yeah?
